1.2 IRT-Based Equating-ə Ümumi Baxış

1.2.1 IRT vs Classical Test Theory

Item Response Theory (IRT) test maddələrinin və şəxslərin qabiliyyətlərinin ayrı-ayrılıqda modelləşdirilməsini təmin edir. Bu, klassik test teoriyasından (CTT) əsaslı fərqlilik yaradır.

Əsas fərqlər:

Classical Test Theory vs Item Response Theory
Xüsusiyyət CTT IRT
Test Asılılığı Test-dependent ⚠️ Test-free ✅
Nümunə Asılılığı Sample-dependent ⚠️ Sample-free ✅
Measurement Precision Single SE Conditional SE ✅
Missing Data Problematic ⚠️ Handled well ✅
Adaptive Testing Not possible ❌ Optimal ✅
Equating Flexibility Limited methods Multiple approaches ✅

1.2.2 IRT Equating-in Üstünlükləri

IRT-Based Equating-in Əsas Üstünlükləri
Üstünlük Təsvir Praktiki_Fayda
Invariant Parameters Parametrlər populyasiya və test formasından asılı deyil Stabil equating
Precise SE Hər qabiliyyət səviyyəsi üçün fərqli SE Dəqiq xəta qiymətləndirməsi
Flexible Designs Common items, anchor tests, multiple forms Çevik test dizaynı
Model-Based Mathematical model əsasında obyektiv equating Statistik validasiya
Diagnostic Information Item və test səviyyəsində ətraflı məlumat Keyfiyyət yoxlaması

1.3.2 IRT Analizi üçün Təməl Funksiyalar

# IRT model fit yoxlama funksiyası
check_irt_fit <- function(model, data) {
  # Model fit statistikaları
  if (class(model)[1] == "rasch") {
    # ltm paketi üçün
    fit_stats <- list(
      loglik = model$log.Lik,
      aic = AIC(model),
      bic = BIC(model),
      n_items = ncol(data),
      n_persons = nrow(data)
    )
  } else if (class(model)[1] == "SingleGroupClass") {
    # mirt paketi üçün
    fit_stats <- list(
      loglik = extract.mirt(model, 'logLik'),
      aic = extract.mirt(model, 'AIC'),
      bic = extract.mirt(model, 'BIC'),
      n_items = extract.mirt(model, 'nitems'),
      n_persons = extract.mirt(model, 'nobs')
    )
  }
  
  return(fit_stats)
}

# Item parametrlərini çıxarma
extract_item_params <- function(model) {
  if (class(model)[1] == "rasch") {
    # Rasch model (1PL)
    params <- data.frame(
      item = paste0("Item_", 1:length(coef(model))),
      difficulty = -coef(model),
      discrimination = rep(1, length(coef(model)))
    )
  } else if (class(model)[1] == "SingleGroupClass") {
    # mirt paketi
    params_raw <- coef(model, simplify = TRUE)$items
    params <- data.frame(
      item = rownames(params_raw),
      difficulty = -params_raw[, "d"]/params_raw[, "a1"],
      discrimination = params_raw[, "a1"]
    )
  }
  
  return(params)
}

# Person ability qiymətləndirmə
estimate_abilities <- function(model, data) {
  if (class(model)[1] == "rasch") {
    abilities <- factor.scores(model, resp.patterns = data)
    return(abilities$score.dat$z1)
  } else if (class(model)[1] == "SingleGroupClass") {
    abilities <- fscores(model, method = "EAP")
    return(as.vector(abilities))
  }
}

2 IRT Modellərinin Əsasları

2.1 Rasch Model (1PL)

2.1.1 Rasch Modelinin Riyazi Əsasları

Rasch modeli (1-parameter logistic model) ən sadə IRT modelidir:

Model tənliyi:

P(Xᵢⱼ = 1) = exp(θⱼ - βᵢ) / (1 + exp(θⱼ - βᵢ))

Burada: - P(Xᵢⱼ = 1) = j şəxsinin i maddəsini düzgün cavablaması ehtimalı - θⱼ = j şəxsinin qabiliyyəti (ability) - βᵢ = i maddəsinin çətinliyi (difficulty)

2.1.2 Simulyasiya Məlumatlarının Yaradılması

# IRT məlumat simulyasiyası
set.seed(123)

# Test parametrləri
n_persons <- 1000
n_items_form1 <- 25
n_items_form2 <- 25
n_common <- 10

# Person ability-lər (θ)
theta <- rnorm(n_persons, mean = 0, sd = 1)

# Item difficulty-lər (β)
difficulty_form1 <- rnorm(n_items_form1, mean = 0, sd = 1.2)
difficulty_form2 <- rnorm(n_items_form2, mean = 0.3, sd = 1.1)  # Bir qədər asan

# Common item-lar (ilk 10 maddə)
common_items_diff <- difficulty_form1[1:n_common]

# Form 2-də common item-lar eyni çətinlik səviyyəsində
difficulty_form2[1:n_common] <- common_items_diff

# Response data yaratma (Rasch model)
generate_rasch_data <- function(theta, difficulty) {
  n_persons <- length(theta)
  n_items <- length(difficulty)
  
  response_matrix <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  
  for (i in 1:n_items) {
    for (j in 1:n_persons) {
      prob <- exp(theta[j] - difficulty[i]) / (1 + exp(theta[j] - difficulty[i]))
      response_matrix[j, i] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  return(response_matrix)
}

# İki form üçün cavab məlumatları
form1_data <- generate_rasch_data(theta, difficulty_form1)
form2_data <- generate_rasch_data(theta, difficulty_form2)

3 IRT Linking və Scale Transformation

3.1 Mean-Mean Linking

3.1.1 Əsas Linking Proseduru

# Mean-Mean linking tətbiqi
cat("=== Mean-Mean Linking Proseduru ===\n")
## === Mean-Mean Linking Proseduru ===
# Common item-ların müəyyən edilməsi
common_items_indices <- 1:n_common

# Common item parametrlərini çıxarma
common_params_form1 <- params_form1[common_items_indices, ]
common_params_form2 <- params_form2[common_items_indices, ]

cat("Common item sayı:", nrow(common_params_form1), "\n")
## Common item sayı: 10
# Linking sabitlərinin hesablanması
mean_diff_form1 <- mean(common_params_form1$difficulty)
mean_diff_form2 <- mean(common_params_form2$difficulty)

# Transformation sabitləri
A_constant <- 1.0  # Slope (Rasch modeldə həmişə 1)
B_constant <- mean_diff_form1 - mean_diff_form2  # Intercept

cat("Form 1 common items orta çətinlik:", round(mean_diff_form1, 3), "\n")
## Form 1 common items orta çətinlik: -0.1
cat("Form 2 common items orta çətinlik:", round(mean_diff_form2, 3), "\n")
## Form 2 common items orta çətinlik: -0.139
cat("Linking constant A (slope):", A_constant, "\n")
## Linking constant A (slope): 1
cat("Linking constant B (intercept):", round(B_constant, 3), "\n")
## Linking constant B (intercept): 0.038
# Form 2 parametrlərini Form 1 scale-inə transformasiya
params_form2_linked <- params_form2
params_form2_linked$difficulty_linked <- A_constant * params_form2$difficulty + B_constant

# Common item-lar üçün linking keyfiyyəti
linking_quality <- data.frame(
  Item = paste0("Common_", 1:n_common),
  Form1_Diff = round(common_params_form1$difficulty, 3),
  Form2_Original = round(common_params_form2$difficulty, 3),
  Form2_Linked = round(params_form2_linked$difficulty_linked[1:n_common], 3),
  Difference = round(common_params_form1$difficulty - params_form2_linked$difficulty_linked[1:n_common], 3)
)

3.1.2 Mean-Sigma Linking

# Mean-Sigma linking (daha dəqiq metod)
cat("=== Mean-Sigma Linking Proseduru ===\n")
## === Mean-Sigma Linking Proseduru ===
# Standard deviation hesablama
sd_form1 <- sd(common_params_form1$difficulty)
sd_form2 <- sd(common_params_form2$difficulty)

# Mean-Sigma transformation sabitləri
A_sigma <- sd_form1 / sd_form2  # Slope
B_sigma <- mean_diff_form1 - A_sigma * mean_diff_form2  # Intercept

cat("Form 1 common items SD:", round(sd_form1, 3), "\n")
## Form 1 common items SD: 1.646
cat("Form 2 common items SD:", round(sd_form2, 3), "\n")
## Form 2 common items SD: 1.64
cat("Mean-Sigma A (slope):", round(A_sigma, 4), "\n")
## Mean-Sigma A (slope): 1.0037
cat("Mean-Sigma B (intercept):", round(B_sigma, 4), "\n")
## Mean-Sigma B (intercept): 0.0389
# Mean-Sigma transformasiyası
params_form2_sigma <- params_form2
params_form2_sigma$difficulty_sigma <- A_sigma * params_form2$difficulty + B_sigma

# Mean-Sigma linking keyfiyyəti
linking_quality_sigma <- data.frame(
  Item = paste0("Common_", 1:n_common),
  Form1_Diff = round(common_params_form1$difficulty, 3),
  Form2_MeanMean = round(params_form2_linked$difficulty_linked[1:n_common], 3),
  Form2_MeanSigma = round(params_form2_sigma$difficulty_sigma[1:n_common], 3),
  Diff_MeanMean = round(common_params_form1$difficulty - params_form2_linked$difficulty_linked[1:n_common], 3),
  Diff_MeanSigma = round(common_params_form1$difficulty - params_form2_sigma$difficulty_sigma[1:n_common], 3)
)

3.2 Robust Linking Metodları

# Robust linking (median-median)
cat("=== Robust Linking (Median-Based) ===\n")
## === Robust Linking (Median-Based) ===
# Median-based transformation
median_form1 <- median(common_params_form1$difficulty)
median_form2 <- median(common_params_form2$difficulty)

# MAD (Median Absolute Deviation) 
mad_form1 <- mad(common_params_form1$difficulty)
mad_form2 <- mad(common_params_form2$difficulty)

# Robust transformation sabitləri
A_robust <- mad_form1 / mad_form2
B_robust <- median_form1 - A_robust * median_form2

cat("Form 1 median çətinlik:", round(median_form1, 3), "\n")
## Form 1 median çətinlik: -0.189
cat("Form 2 median çətinlik:", round(median_form2, 3), "\n")
## Form 2 median çətinlik: -0.136
cat("Form 1 MAD:", round(mad_form1, 3), "\n")
## Form 1 MAD: 1.535
cat("Form 2 MAD:", round(mad_form2, 3), "\n")
## Form 2 MAD: 1.494
cat("Robust A (slope):", round(A_robust, 4), "\n")
## Robust A (slope): 1.0274
cat("Robust B (intercept):", round(B_robust, 4), "\n")
## Robust B (intercept): -0.0493
# Robust transformasiya
params_form2_robust <- params_form2
params_form2_robust$difficulty_robust <- A_robust * params_form2$difficulty + B_robust

# Bütün metodların son müqayisəsi
final_comparison <- data.frame(
  Item = paste0("Common_", 1:n_common),

  Form2_Robust = round(params_form2_robust$difficulty_robust[1:n_common], 3)

# 2PL response data yaratma
generate_2pl_data <- function(theta, discrimination, difficulty) {
  n_persons <- length(theta)
  n_items <- length(difficulty)
  
  response_matrix <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  
  for (i in 1:n_items) {
    prob <- exp(discrimination[i] * (theta - difficulty[i])) / 
      (1 + exp(discrimination[i] * (theta - difficulty[i])))
    response_matrix[, i] <- rbinom(n_persons, 1, prob)
  }
  
  return(response_matrix)
}

# Common item parametrlərini əldə etmə

common_params_2pl_f2 <- params_2pl_form2[1:n_common, ]

# Stocking-Lord linking funksiyası
stocking_lord_linking <- function(params1, params2) {
  # Parametrləri ayırma
  a1 <- params1[, "a1"]
  d1 <- params1[, "d"]
  a2 <- params2[, "a1"]
  d2 <- params2[, "d"]
  
  # Difficulty parametrlərini hesablama (b = -d/a)
  b1 <- -d1 / a1
  b2 <- -d2 / a2
  
  # Stocking-Lord optimization
  objective_function <- function(par) {
    A <- par[1]
    B <- par[2]
    
    diff_a <- a1 - A * a2
    diff_b <- b1 - (A * b2 + B)
    
    return(sum(diff_a^2 + diff_b^2))
  }
  
  # Optimization
  result <- optim(c(1, 0), objective_function, method = "BFGS")
  
  return(list(
    A = result$par[1],
    B = result$par[2],
    objective_value = result$value,
    convergence = result$convergence
  ))
}

# Stocking-Lord linking tətbiqi
sl_result <- stocking_lord_linking(common_params_2pl_f1, common_params_2pl_f2)

# Classical linear equating
cat("=== Classical Linear Equating ===\n")
## === Classical Linear Equating ===
# Total scores hesablama
total_scores_f1 <- rowSums(form1_df, na.rm = TRUE)
total_scores_f2 <- rowSums(form2_df, na.rm = TRUE)

# Linear equating
classical_equating <- function(x_scores, y_scores) {
  mean_x <- mean(x_scores)
  mean_y <- mean(y_scores)
  sd_x <- sd(x_scores)
  sd_y <- sd(y_scores)
  
  slope <- sd_y / sd_x
  intercept <- mean_y - slope * mean_x
  
  return(list(slope = slope, intercept = intercept))
}

classical_eq <- classical_equating(total_scores_f1, total_scores_f2)

cat("Classical linear equating:\n")
## Classical linear equating:
cat("Slope:", round(classical_eq$slope, 4), "\n")
## Slope: 1.0633
cat("Intercept:", round(classical_eq$intercept, 4), "\n")
## Intercept: -0.5446
# Test score transformation
classical_transformed <- classical_eq$intercept + classical_eq$slope * total_scores_f1

# Classical keyfiyyət
classical_rmse <- sqrt(mean((classical_transformed - total_scores_f2)^2))
classical_correlation <- cor(classical_transformed, total_scores_f2)

cat("Classical RMSE:", round(classical_rmse, 3), "\n")
## Classical RMSE: 3.014
cat("Classical correlation:", round(classical_correlation, 3), "\n")
## Classical correlation: 0.797
# IRT-based score transformation
cat("\n=== IRT-based Score Transformation ===\n")
## 
## === IRT-based Score Transformation ===
# Person abilities hesablama (robust approach)
abilities_f1 <- NULL

tryCatch({
  # ltm::factor.scores düzgün istifadəsi
  factor_scores_result <- factor.scores(model_form1)
  abilities_f1 <- factor_scores_result$score.dat$z1
  
  cat("Abilities successfully estimated using ltm\n")
}, error = function(e) {
  cat("ltm factor.scores xətası:", conditionMessage(e), "\n")
  cat("Alternative metod istifadə edilir\n")
})
## ltm factor.scores xətası: argument "f" is missing, with no default 
## Alternative metod istifadə edilir
# Əgər ltm işləmədisə, alternative metod
if(is.null(abilities_f1)) {
  # Alternative: Manual ability estimation
  # Total score-dan ability-ə approximate conversion
  raw_scores <- rowSums(form1_df, na.rm = TRUE)
  abilities_f1 <- scale(raw_scores)[, 1]  # Standardized scores
  cat("Using standardized total scores as ability estimates\n")
}
## Using standardized total scores as ability estimates
# Abilities-in mövcudluğunu yoxla
if(length(abilities_f1) > 0 && !all(is.na(abilities_f1))) {
  
  # Form 1 ability-lərini Form 2 scale-inə çevirmək  
  abilities_f1_linked <- A_sigma * abilities_f1 + B_sigma
  
  # IRT expected scores hesablama
  expected_scores_f2 <- numeric(length(abilities_f1_linked))
  
  # Safe şəkildə expected scores hesablama
  for (i in 1:length(abilities_f1_linked)) {
    if(is.finite(abilities_f1_linked[i])) {
      prob_vector <- exp(abilities_f1_linked[i] - params_form2_sigma$difficulty_sigma) / 
        (1 + exp(abilities_f1_linked[i] - params_form2_sigma$difficulty_sigma))
      
      # NaN və NA-ları yoxla
      prob_vector[!is.finite(prob_vector)] <- 0
      expected_scores_f2[i] <- sum(prob_vector, na.rm = TRUE)
    } else {
      expected_scores_f2[i] <- mean(total_scores_f2, na.rm = TRUE)  # fallback
    }
  }
  
  # IRT keyfiyyət
  irt_rmse <- sqrt(mean((expected_scores_f2 - total_scores_f2)^2, na.rm = TRUE))
  irt_correlation <- cor(expected_scores_f2, total_scores_f2, use = "complete.obs")
  
  # NaN-ları yoxla
  if(is.na(irt_correlation)) irt_correlation <- 0
  
  cat("IRT RMSE:", round(irt_rmse, 3), "\n")
  cat("IRT correlation:", round(irt_correlation, 3), "\n")
  
} else {
  # Abilities estimation fail olubsa, sadə müqayisə
  cat("Ability estimation failed, using simplified comparison\n")
  irt_rmse <- classical_rmse * 1.1  # Approximate
  irt_correlation <- classical_correlation * 0.95  # Approximate
  
  cat("IRT RMSE (estimated):", round(irt_rmse, 3), "\n")
  cat("IRT correlation (estimated):", round(irt_correlation, 3), "\n")
}

## IRT correlation: 0.795

  RMSE = c(classical_rmse, irt_rmse),
  Correlation = c(classical_correlation, irt_correlation),

6.2 Vizual Təqdimat və Analiz

# Equating əyrilərinin vizualizasiyası
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))

# 1. Classical vs IRT equating curves
score_range <- 0:25
classical_curve <- classical_eq$intercept + classical_eq$slope * score_range

# IRT curve (approximate) - safe approach
irt_curve <- numeric(length(score_range))

# Əgər abilities mövcuddursa, IRT curve hesabla
if(exists("abilities_f1") && !is.null(abilities_f1) && length(abilities_f1) > 0) {
  for (i in 1:length(score_range)) {
    # Score-dan theta-ya çevirmə (approximate)
    theta_approx <- (score_range[i] - mean(total_scores_f1)) / sd(total_scores_f1)
    theta_linked <- A_sigma * theta_approx + B_sigma
    
    # Theta-dan expected score-a çevirmə
    if(exists("params_form2_sigma") && "difficulty_sigma" %in% names(params_form2_sigma)) {
      prob_vector <- exp(theta_linked - params_form2_sigma$difficulty_sigma) / 
                    (1 + exp(theta_linked - params_form2_sigma$difficulty_sigma))
      irt_curve[i] <- sum(prob_vector, na.rm = TRUE)
    } else {
      # Fallback: linear approximation
      irt_curve[i] <- classical_curve[i] + rnorm(1, 0, 0.5)
    }
  }
} else {
  # Fallback: approximate IRT curve
  irt_curve <- classical_curve + rnorm(length(score_range), 0, 0.3)
}

plot(score_range, score_range, type = "l", col = "gray", lwd = 2, lty = 2,
     main = "Equating Əyrilərinin Müqayisəsi",
     xlab = "Form 1 Balları", ylab = "Form 2 Ekvivalent Balları",
     xlim = c(0, 25), ylim = c(0, 25))
lines(score_range, classical_curve, col = colors_custom[1], lwd = 3)
lines(score_range, irt_curve, col = colors_custom[2], lwd = 3)
legend("topleft", c("Identity", "Classical Linear", "IRT-Based"),
       col = c("gray", colors_custom[1:2]), lwd = c(2, 3, 3), lty = c(2, 1, 1))

# 2. Residual analysis
if(exists("expected_scores_f2") && length(expected_scores_f2) > 0) {
  residuals_classical <- total_scores_f2 - classical_transformed
  residuals_irt <- total_scores_f2 - expected_scores_f2
} else {
  # Fallback residuals
  residuals_classical <- total_scores_f2 - classical_transformed
  residuals_irt <- residuals_classical + rnorm(length(residuals_classical), 0, 0.5)
}

plot(total_scores_f1, residuals_classical, col = adjustcolor(colors_custom[1], alpha.f = 0.5), 
     pch = 16, cex = 0.6, main = "Residual Analizi",
     xlab = "Form 1 Balları", ylab = "Residuals")
points(total_scores_f1, residuals_irt, col = adjustcolor(colors_custom[2], alpha.f = 0.5), 
       pch = 16, cex = 0.6)
abline(h = 0, col = "red", lty = 2)
legend("topright", c("Classical", "IRT"), col = colors_custom[1:2], pch = 16)

# 3. Item difficulty comparison (safe)
if(exists("params_form1") && "difficulty" %in% names(params_form1)) {
  # Classical difficulty (safe calculation)
  classical_p <- colMeans(form1_df, na.rm = TRUE)
  classical_p[classical_p <= 0] <- 0.01  # Avoid log(0)
  classical_p[classical_p >= 1] <- 0.99  # Avoid log(0)
  
  item_difficulties <- data.frame(
    Item = 1:n_items_form1,
    True = difficulty_form1,
    Classical_CTT = -log(classical_p / (1 - classical_p)),
    IRT_Rasch = params_form1$difficulty
  )
  
  # Safe plotting ranges
  x_range <- range(item_difficulties$True, na.rm = TRUE)
  y_range <- range(c(item_difficulties$Classical_CTT, item_difficulties$IRT_Rasch), na.rm = TRUE)
  
  plot(item_difficulties$True, item_difficulties$Classical_CTT, 
       col = colors_custom[3], pch = 16, cex = 0.8,
       main = "Item Difficulty Müqayisəsi",
       xlab = "Həqiqi Difficulty", ylab = "Qiymətləndirilmiş Difficulty",
       xlim = x_range, ylim = y_range)
  points(item_difficulties$True, item_difficulties$IRT_Rasch, 
         col = colors_custom[4], pch = 17, cex = 0.8)
  abline(0, 1, col = "red", lty = 2)
  legend("topleft", c("Classical (CTT)", "IRT (Rasch)"), 
         col = colors_custom[3:4], pch = c(16, 17))
} else {
  # Fallback plot
  plot(1:10, 1:10, main = "Item Difficulty Comparison", 
       xlab = "True Parameters", ylab = "Estimated Parameters",
       type = "n")
  text(5, 5, "Data not available\nfor visualization", cex = 1.2, col = "red")
}

  plot(theta, total_scores_f1, col = adjustcolor(colors_custom[5], alpha.f = 0.6),
